The '''Pohnpei flycatcher''' ('''''Myiagra pluto'''''), known  as Koikoi in [[Pohnpeian language|Pohnpeian]], is a species of [[bird]] in the family [[Monarchidae]]. It is [[Endemism|endemic]] to [[Micronesia]] and can be found on the [[Caroline Islands]].

==Taxonomy and systematics==
Some authorities consider the Pohnpei flycatcher to be a subspecies of the [[oceanic flycatcher]]. Alternate names include the '''Pohnpei broadbill''', '''Ponape broadbill''', '''Ponape flycatcher''' and '''Ponape Myiagra flycatcher'''.

